<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
Response — defaultMappingReturned when civic coverage lookup cannot resolve.

When Gate 2 produces a non-conforming result AND the civic coverage region lookup
does not resolve to a single unambiguous boundary, the LVF must construct a
synthetic default mapping and emit the <defaultMappingReturned> warning.

This request submits a completely out-of-coverage address (country=CA, which has
no provisioned service boundary and no civic coverage region entry). Gate 2 fails
at ca:country (no SSAP or RCL records match CA). The civic coverage lookup also
fails because no entry exists for country=CA. The synthetic default mapping
(displayName="VALIDATION RESULT ONLY", sourceId={00000000-...}, expires=NO-EXPIRATION)
is returned with <defaultMappingReturned> present in <warnings>.

This confirms the complete fallback path: non-conforming result + coverage miss
+ synthetic mapping + warning emission.
-->
<findService xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:lost1" validateLocation="true">
  <location id="L1" profile="civic">
    <civicAddress xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:pidf:geopriv10:civicAddr">
      <country>CA</country>
      <A1>ON</A1>
      <A2>York Region</A2>
      <A3>Markham</A3>
      <RD>Main</RD>
      <STS>Street</STS>
      <HNO>100</HNO>
    </civicAddress>
  </location>
  <service>urn:service:sos</service>
</findService>
